BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:resmtl-11
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260512T041731
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260514T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260514T190000
SUMMARY:Constellation: Bike ride to sketchy beach (3rd annual!)
LOCATION:2515 Rue Delisle (métro lionel-groulx)
DESCRIPTION:2026-05-14 17:00:00\n\n2515 Rue Delisle (métro lionel-groulx)
 \n\nhttps://www.openstreetmap.org/way/347696464\n\nIt's BACK! The Constell
 ation kick off bike ride/beach hang :)\nWe meet outside the front door of 
 CEDA! Look for bikes!\nMeet at 5pm\, departure at 530pm SHARP\nWe will rid
 e bikes to a sketchy beach on the voie maritime. This is off the island of
  Montreal. The sketchy beach is magical. There is best view of the city an
 d the sunset. There are no laws. There are no cops. There are no tourists.
  (There are no bathrooms)\nRAIN OR SHINE. Last year there were thunderstor
 ms up until the moment we departed. Those of us that stuck it out were tre
 ated to the most breathtaking sunset of the year!\nThe bike ride is about 
 12kms and is mostly flat. We can ride bikes the whole way there. At the en
 d we have to descend a small steep hill and short walk along a path to the
  water. The accessibility of this terrain depends greatly on the weather i
 mmediately before the event (it could be muddy\, slippery\, overgrown\, or
  dry and very passable).\nWe don't know what beach we will exactly end up 
 on\, as this depends on the conditions the day of (and if anyone is alread
 y there before us!)\nIf you'd like to join us later\, you'll have to conta
 ct someone who's there. Or just come out and try to find us! We should arr
 ive by 6:30.\nInstead of biking you can get there by walking\, or taking p
 ublic transit part of the way and then walking 6-8 kms (far).\nBeing a ske
 tchy beach\, there are no bathrooms\, no running water\, no services of an
 y kind. The nearest store is 10kms away.\nPrepare for the weather! Sometim
 es it's buggy\, so having long sleeves and pants and a face covering for t
 he last part of the ride can be desirable. Sometimes it's warm and you can
  swim (if you dare!). It can cold when the sun goes down. There can be poi
 son ivy\, depending on how the spring has been going.\nThings to bring:\nW
 ater\nSnacks\nFirewood?\nMore water\nSunscreen (if sunny)\nLong sleeves an
 d pants (if cool and/or buggy)\nBugspray\nLights for the ride home\nFriend
 s\nSwimming gear (if you wanna swim)\nSomething to sit on\nToilet paper\nF
 riends!\nGames!
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.openstreetmap.org/way/347696464
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:resmtl-12
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260512T041731
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260514T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260514T200000
SUMMARY:Cercle de lecture : Rosa Luxembourg - Réforme ou Révolution ?
LOCATION:1710 Rue Beaudry (métro Beaudry)
DESCRIPTION:2026-05-14 18:00:00\n\n1710 Rue Beaudry (métro Beaudry)\n\nht
 tps://www.openstreetmap.org/way/181295868\n\nLe Centre Internationaliste R
 yerson – Fondation aubin (CIRFA) vous invites à participer à son proch
 ain cercle de lecture autour du livre Réforme ou révolution de Rosa Luxe
 mbourg. Le livre est un classique du marxisme et un excellent ouvrage pour
  découvrir la pensée de Rosa Luxembourg.\nLien vers notre site : https:/
 /centreinternationalisterfa.org/reforme-ou.../\nRésumé du livre : En 189
 7\, la controverse du révisionnisme éclate dans le mouvement marxiste. 
 Édouard Bernstein\, ancien secrétaire d’Engels\, veut donner une nouve
 lle interprétation du marxisme qui abandonne la révolution au profit de 
 la réforme sociale. Face à cette monstrueuse déformation du marxisme\, 
 une jeune marxiste encore peu connue\, Rosa Luxembourg\, va relever le dé
 fi de réfuter les thèses révisionnistes pour défendre la révolution\,
  le marxisme orthodoxe et l’effondrement du capitalisme.\nChaque semaine
  nous nous réunirons pour discuter une partie du livre. Les séances se d
 érouleront du 7 mai au 11 juin 2026 et se tiendront tous les jeudis de 18
 h à 20h au 1710 Beaudry salle 2.10.\nL’événement est gratuit et ouver
 t à tous.\nLe texte est disponible gratuitement en ligne (https://www.mar
 xists.org/.../luxembur/works/1898/index.html).\nNous espérons vous voir p
 articiper en grand nombre.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.openstreetmap.org/way/181295868
END:VEVENT
