SUMMARY:Dick's book club
LOCATION:633 avenue Beaumont
DESCRIPTION:2026-05-23 15:00:00\n\n633 avenue Beaumont\n\nhttps://www.open
 streetmap.org/node/11973025945\n\nWe’re so excited to announce our book 
 club! Join us as a part of the inaugural Lire Queer Reader Fest to discuss
  a selection of writing from Gendertrash From Hell (LittlePuss Press\, 202
 5)\, edited by Mirha-Soleil Ross. &nbsp\;\nOriginally published in the ear
 ly nineties by Mirha-Soleil Ross and Xanthra Phillippa MacKay\, Gendertras
 h From Hell includes all four published issues and a fifth unfinished issu
 e of the self-titled zine\, which assembled poetry\, articles\, short stor
 ies\, interviews\, and visual art “devoted to the issues and concerns of
  transsexuals.” Poems about gendercide and sex-work decriminalization\, 
 self-blessing rituals and tips for safe electrolysis\, comics and collages
  about transphobia within queer communities\, and articles on trans-specif
 ic health care and the impacts of AIDS on transsexuals — all of these an
 d more can be found in the pages of this much beloved part of trans print 
 culture.\nThis book club meeting is a one-time-only event and will be faci
 litated by Jeanne Roberge. We recommend that participants read the first a
 nd fourth issues of the zine. Digital copies of Gendertrash 1-4 are freely
  available on the Arquives website.\nRegister here&nbsp\;: https://docs.go
 ogle.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSemPaNw8_111x-WGPLEBmAMyaPtPoGLpijOQXBamEFHkl2x1
 g/viewform&nbsp\;\nWe can’t wait to see you there.&nbsp\;\nEvent details
